-- Singapore Stocks: Ezra Holdings, Keppel Corp., Thai Beverage
-- B y   J o n a t h a n   B u r g o s
-- 2012-01-10T09:41:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-10/singapore-stocks-ezra-holdings-keppel-corp-thai-beverage.html
Singapore’s  Straits Times Index (FSSTI) 
gained 1.1 percent to 2,719.83, the highest close since Dec. 8.
Eight shares rose for each that fell in the 30-member gauge.  Singapore’s stock-market valuations are “pretty cheap,”
said Garry Evans, head of global equity strategy at HSBC
Holdings Plc, at a briefing in Singapore. Shares on the
benchmark Straits Times Index are trading at 1.2 times estimated
book value, compared with 1.5 times for the  MSCI Asia Pacific
Excluding Japan Index. (MXAPJ)   The following were among the most active shares in the
market. Stock symbols are in parentheses after the company
names.  Ezra Holdings Ltd. (EZRA)  , a provider of offshore
logistics services for the oil and gas industry, climbed 5.6
percent to 94 Singapore cents. The company said its EMAS AMC
subsea construction unit won two contracts, valued at as much as
600 million Norwegian Krone ($100 million), from Statoil ASA.  Keppel Corp. (KEP)  , the world’s biggest builder of oil
rigs, gained 4.1 percent to S$9.94 after saying its Keppel
AmFELS Inc. unit won a $150 million contract from Diamond
Offshore Drilling Inc.  KSH Holdings Ltd. (KSHH)   advanced 4.9 percent to 21.5
Singapore cents after the construction company said it was
contracted to a S$110 million ($85 million) condominium project
in the eastern Singapore town of Pasir Ris.  Thai Beverage Pcl (THBEV SP), Thailand’s largest beer and
whiskey maker, added 4 percent to 26 Singapore cents. The stock
rose after Maxtop Management Corp., a company owned by Thai
Beverage controlling shareholder Charoen Sirivadhanabhakdi,
bought two million of the brewer’s shares at 25.392  Singapore 
cents each, raising its stake to 17.17 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
